storyInfo: Kawalerielki's Infected are secretly evacuating for a fourth time, but a little girl has gone missing. Fartooth must find Zola and confront the common question posed to them all: What is home?

attributes.content: 'You will come back? Really? After you become a knight?'
'It's a promise then. We'll wait for you to come home, showered in glory, and then we'll spread the word that our town is the home of the Justyna, the knight!'
My... home.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Careful.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Sorry.
attributes.name: Carefree Boy

attributes.content: I've never seen you in the village. Are you from outside?
attributes.name: Carefree Boy

attributes.content: I was born here. Then I went to Kawalerielki.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Kawalerielki! Are you a knight?
attributes.name: Carefree Boy

attributes.content: You must be! Your armor looks much better than the wooden stuff Hubert makes.
attributes.name: Carefree Boy

attributes.content: Can I see your crossbow?
attributes.name: Carefree Boy

attributes.content: Millen! Stop bothering people!
attributes.name: Kind Villager

attributes.content: I'm sorry, the boy's been reading too many knight novels lately. The questions flow nonstop when he meets someone from out of town.
attributes.name: Kind Villager

attributes.content: Wait, is it just me... or do you look familiar...?
attributes.name: Kind Villager

attributes.content: Aunt Danka.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Justyna...? You're really back... oh, I suppose it's Fartooth Knight now.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: We saw the news about your title. Everyone's happy for you.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: You remember old Cole? He saves clippings of every headline about you on his wall.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: He opens a bottle whenever you win a competition—probably just an excuse for him to drink more.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.text: The woman carefully scans Justyna, looking for something—perhaps expecting to see something.
Justyna is familiar with this look.
She has seen it many times in Kawalerielki, from opponents, spectators, reporters... countless eyes looking, searching, just to see—

attributes.content: You got sick... we heard about it on the news. Everyone in the village is worried.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: It's under control.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Very good, very good.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: What's that in your hand, Millen?
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: The knight's quiver.
attributes.name: Millen

attributes.content: Don't touch that!
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: Err, I mean... give it back to Fartooth Knight. It's very expensive.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: It's dangerous, even if it won't hurt you.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: I'm sorry, I should be more considerate.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Do you want to sit a spell, Fartooth Knight? We've all missed you. I'll just need to give them a heads-up... to prepare properly.
attributes.name: Aunt Danka

attributes.content: What are you standing there for, Fartooth?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: We have to count the Infected after the evacuation.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: ...Group Two, all accounted for.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: (When did she count them? She was definitely daydreaming.)
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Has anyone seen Zola? Where did she go?
attributes.name: Anxious Man

attributes.content: Is something wrong, Mr. Farone?
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: I think Zola went out to take a look at the new camp, but she's not back yet.
attributes.name: Farone

attributes.content: Did anyone see her when we moved over from Residential Sector 9?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: I wasn't paying attention... it was still dark, and I was leading the way for a villager with a bad leg...
attributes.name: Farone

attributes.content: Don't worry, we'll find her, but we need to narrow down the area. There are a lot of buildings between the two sectors.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Sona...
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: I may know where the girl went.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: The day before...
Hello again, friends.
attributes.name: Cheerful Infected

attributes.content: How many times has it been in the last six months?
attributes.name: Infected Knight

attributes.content: This is the fourth.
attributes.name: Cheerful Infected

attributes.content: It's been a long stay in this abandoned industrial area, all things considered. Three full months since the last evacuation.
attributes.name: Cheerful Infected

attributes.content: I still remember that time the Armorless Union came knocking just a few days after we settled down. Since then, I've kept my stuff down to what I can fit in a couple of bags, ready to leave at a moment's notice.
attributes.name: Cheerful Infected

attributes.content: Sorry, folks. Sona's working to find a place you can stay for the long haul.
attributes.name: Infected Knight

attributes.content: It's not your fault. It's all thanks to Pinus Sylvestris that we're still able to stay in Kawalerielki at all. Besides, where can a bunch of Infected go?
attributes.name: Cheerful Infected

attributes.content: We got used to it when we wandered the edge of the nomadic plate. But Zola didn't like it, and even had a fight with Mr. Farone over it in the morning.
attributes.name: Cheerful Infected

attributes.content: The General Chamber of Commerce crackdown is intensifying. Not just the commercial plates; the residential areas aren't safe anymore.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Armorless Union patrols have been spotted on the streets nearby. Not many, but it's a warning sign.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: I say we pound 'em flat and show those empty suits this is Pinus Sylvestris turf.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: And give them an excuse to blow up our factory while we're short-handed?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: What do you think, Justyna?
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: ...It's just an abandoned factory.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: That's right! We'll find another place nearby—
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: ...It's not home.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Their home was destroyed in a Catastrophe. They should move to a safer place, so that more may live.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Fartooth!
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: We don't have what it takes to butt heads with the GCC directly, not yet. Maybe someday we'll have our own plate, and every Infected in Kawalerielki will have a home to go back.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: We are setting out first thing tomorrow morning. Ashley and I know the routes best, so we'll lead the pack. Iwona, you clear any obstacles. Justyna, you're on recon duty.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: As for tonight—
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: I'll keep watch.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.text: The abandoned factory is located in Residential Sector 9, underneath Commercial Sectors 5 and 11, on the edge of the nomadic plate, where energy is always at a premium.

Justyna has crossed paths with these refugees quite a few times since she joined Pinus Sylvestris. They laugh at their rotten luck; they have been on the move more than any other Infected group receiving protection.
Justyna does not know how long they have been away from home. Sona told her that one of the older members carried a bag of crop seeds for the last evacuation; this time, he has thrown it away.
But would their village have been their home, even if it was not destroyed by Catastrophe?
'Do you want to sit a spell, Fartooth Knight?'
Justyna hums a tune from her hometown, and the noisy, sorrowful winds of Kawalerielki hum with her.

attributes.content: Is that...?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: ...Zola?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Those people in black weren't here in this alley a few days ago...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: No, I'll be late if I take any more detours. I'll have to...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: What are you doing here?
Mmph—
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Don't leave the camp at night. It's dangerous.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Justyna...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I'll take you back.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: No, no! Rita's waiting for me!
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Rita?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Don't tell Mr. Farone, please. He'll be mad if he finds out I'm friends with a kid from the residential district.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: But Rita's a good girl, really. She doesn't care about my sickness, she says I'm good at drawing...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Why do we have to move all the time, Justyna?
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I am the same as everybody else when I wrap myself up. Nobody found out I was sick when Rita took me into a shop.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I don't want to move again...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: After the village got destroyed, we drifted around the wilderness, slowly running out of food.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: We were only able to get into Kawalerielki because Mr. Farone found Sona.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: But we're still drifting. We just do it underground now.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I can barely remember the berries that grew on the trees of the village. I used to love them so much...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: We wouldn't be like this if the village was still around.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Is there anywhere the Infected can go at all...?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Was your home destroyed by Catastrophe too?
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: No, that village has not faced a single Catastrophe in its entire history.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Sounds nice... where is it? Is it pretty?
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: It sits in the north, where the forest meets the plains.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: It is... a beautiful place.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: What's your hometown like, Justyna? Tell me all about it!
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Maybe next time.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Who's there?
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin

attributes.content: A third patrol?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Come in, patrol... come in... do you require backup...?
attributes.name: Voice from the Communicator

attributes.content: We need to move.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: But I haven't said goodbye to Rita yet...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I told her not to play with uninfected children!
attributes.name: Farone

attributes.content: There are no kids Zola's age in the camp. She's lonely.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: The Armorless Union doesn't care that she's a child.
attributes.name: Infected Knight

attributes.content: She's Infected. To them, young doesn't mean innocent; it just means easier cleanup.
attributes.name: Infected Knight

attributes.content: Justyna. How sure are you about Zola?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: ...I can't be sure.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: We ruffled feathers when we got out of Sector 9. The Armorless Union is probably watching the warehouse right now. Scouts, troopers... they'll be out in force.
attributes.name: Infected Knight

attributes.content: It's not just this district that we have to protect. There's another group of refugees who just arrived at the outskirts of Kawalerielki today, waiting for our escort.
attributes.name: Infected Knight

attributes.content: I thought I heard something in that storage room. Should we check it out?
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin A

attributes.content: In an abandoned warehouse like this, there're bound to be critters crawling around. I'm not going in there.
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin B

attributes.content: The storage room... that's where Zola was drawing her pictures!
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Green... red stripes...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Yes, yes... and yellow, just like her eyes.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: There's a pattern on her quiver, and shiny bolts inside.
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Justyna's an amazing shot... one bolt, and all the bad guys in black scatter...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: No need to be scared... no need to be scared...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: The scope's in the wrong place.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: I couldn't aim properly if it were so far forward.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Justyna!
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I... I'm so sorry... I just wanted to get the parting gift I made for Rita...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I wanted to keep it... even if I couldn't give it to her...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: You'll meet again.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Let's get out of here. Can you walk?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: I twisted my ankle when I came in... I'm sorry... I'm so scared...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: It's okay. No need to apologize.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Close your eyes, Zola.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: But...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: Yesterday, you asked me what my hometown was like.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Close your eyes, and I'll tell you all about it.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.text: The smell of haystacks.
The untrimmed stalks sting a little. Lie upon them, and all you see is the clear blue sky.
The sound of the flowing waves of wheat.
A bug buzzing in the air—

attributes.content: Wh-What's that sound?!
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: A-Are you okay, Justyna?
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: I'm fine. Keep your eyes shut.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: The bug lands on a wheat stalk. The harvest sickle swings, and it dives into the soil.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: And the wind.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: The melody on the wind is the little tune that Uncle Cole liked to play.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: That's my... home.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: (The reinforcements came quickly. It's going to be hard to get through the front door carrying Zola...)
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: What was that sound?
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin

attributes.content: We're under attack! This is where the Infected knights have been harboring the refugees. Be on your guard!
attributes.name: Voice from the Communicator

attributes.content: (Come on, Justyna... you've faced down multiple enemies in the tourneys... you can think of something...)
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: ...Wild Mane?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: So many assassins to guard one abandoned warehouse. Since when is the GCC in the business of bleeding money?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: You think you can take us all by yourself?
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin

attributes.content: Hmph, one more helper won't make a difference—
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin

attributes.content: You're rushing too far ahead, Wild Mane!
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: That's what being a lancer is all about—charging into the fray and messing up enemy formations! Standard tactics.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Then what's the point of making a plan?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: Got to adapt to change.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Ashley means you're too far from the formation for her to protect you with her shield.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: That's not what I said!
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: We're here to get Justyna, aren't we? Where is she?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: There.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: You were right, Justyna. You found Zola.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Thanks... all of you.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: You're welcome.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: The rest of the knights are off to help our new friends. We were always going to hold back here.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: I just didn't expect you to charge even faster than me.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: We haven't talked much, but I think I like you!
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: More guys coming in, eleven o'clock and two o'clock.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Ashley—
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: They're too scattered. I don't have enough ammo left.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: Leave it to me.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: They have a sniper! Form up, don't get picked off!
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin

attributes.content: Thanks.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: Good job.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Front door's open. All the Armorless Union assassins in the factory are down.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Communications equipment's dealt with. There won't be any more reinforcements for a while.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: Something isn't right.
Zola? You can open your eyes now. A pity you missed the fight, but you are too young for this.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: The wind isn't right.
Justyna? What's the matter?
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Argh—
attributes.name: Armorless Union Assassin

attributes.content: Phew, that was close.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Didn't see that sniper up there.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: How'd you spot him, Justyna?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: I couldn't hear the sound of the wind.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: Well... there's a window there. Wind affects the trajectory of a projectile.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: I'm guessing you didn't get it either.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: You'll get used to the way Justyna talks soon enough.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Zola.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Justyna...
attributes.name: Zola

attributes.content: It's safe now.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Let's go home.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.text: Justyna climbs the observation deck. Wind whirls through the streets, through gaps in the sewer pipes, swaying the less-than-sturdy scaffolding.
Back at the camp, Farone scolds Zola for running out on her own. Seeing her teacher's mouth twitch with fear and worry, Zola does not argue and simply grips the hands of her loved ones.

All of them will go into dreamland, not thinking about when the next evacuation might be, not asking whether this nomadic life might ever come to an end. Home is where they have made their beds from cardboard boxes and clothes.
Once again, she takes out her flute.
Brr—

attributes.content: 'Beep beep'—
What's that?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: (Inquisitive beeping)
attributes.name: 'Justice Knight'

attributes.content: Wild Mane's... pet?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: (Joyous beeping)
attributes.name: 'Justice Knight'

attributes.content: (Cheerful beeping)
attributes.name: 'Justice Knight'

attributes.content: Hey, stop! You'll wake everyone up!
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: Where's the switch?
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.text: The Liberi fumbles with the unfamiliar beeping machine, dropping her flute to the ground.
Apparently sensing her predicament, Justice Knight considerately spins around and turns on its searchlight.
No, no... Justyna tries to block the light with her body, and realizes that Justice Knight is taller than she.

attributes.content: The switch is behind the plate.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: ...Thanks.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: I wouldn't recommend shutting her off, though. Justice Knight gets lonely when she can't get a signal around her.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: You like to be with people, don't you?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: (Joyous beeping)
attributes.name: 'Justice Knight'

attributes.content: Hey, Justyna... what's that sound? I've never heard it before...
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: It's my flute.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: You play the flute?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Oh... I see.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: You had Justice put out a call because you wanted an audience, didn't you?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Well, you've found one. I don't know much about music, but I'm a great listener.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Go ahead and play, Fartooth Knight.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: You just wanted to get in on the action.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: Greynuty?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Did Justice wake you up too?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: No, YOU woke me up.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: You should thank me, then. Justyna is putting on a show.
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Don't pressure her... is that a flute?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: I used to live near an old woman with a bad leg. I could hear her playing in her house, one of these hand-made flutes.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: Now I'm starting to miss the traditional melodies from back in the day.
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: What's that? An attic party, and I wasn't invited?
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: And there I was, thinking I was giving you a bit more sleep after that rescue operation.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: You got woken up too?
attributes.name: Greynuty

attributes.content: I was thinking about Zola.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Iwona's right. We can't hide underground forever.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: People have gotten so used to the nomadic life that they're beginning to forget even the Infected deserve to have a home.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Come down and hear out my new idea, since you're up anyway.
attributes.name: Sona

attributes.content: Sure.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: What about the show?
attributes.name: Iwona

attributes.content: Maybe next time, Iwona.
attributes.name: Justyna

attributes.content: I'll play you a song from home.
attributes.name: Justyna
